Peru Stocks: Aceros Arequipa, Casa Grande, Siderperu, Telefonica

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-04-26T20:40:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/peru-stocks-aceros-arequipa-casa-grande-siderperu-telefonica.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index dropped 2.3 percent to 17,765.63.
The MSCI All Peru Capped Index fell 2 percent to 2,453.55.  Utilities and industrial stocks dropped on investor concern
over the outcome of the June 5 elections, said Ernesto Ferrand,
a trader at Lima-based brokerage Andes Securities SAB.  Telefonica del Peru SAA (TELEFBC1)  (TELEFBC1 PE), the local unit of
Telefonica SA, plunged 8.4 percent to 2.50 soles. Corp. Aceros
Arequipa SA (CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based steelmaker, fell for a
fifth session, losing 7 percent to 2.14 soles.  Empresa
Siderurgica del Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of Gerdau SA known
as Siderperu, dropped 5.3 percent to 1.08 soles. Refineria la
Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s Repsol YPF SA known
as Relapasa, fell 3.7 percent to 1.29 soles as crude declined in
New York.  Sugar producers slumped after prices dropped for a second
session in New York.  Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer
and a unit of Gloria SA, fell 5.4 percent to 11.59 soles.
Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POMALCC1 PE), a unit of Grupo
Oviedo, dropped 4.4 percent to 43 centimos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
